div.p:
Be not aſhamed Sir to charge home, deſcend from your mighty mouthing Generalls, your pretended fierce, furious, contradicting, blaſpeming, helliſh ſpeeches (words not beſeeming ſo mild a mouth as a Miniſters ought to be) to plaine particulars; ſpare neither our perſons, words nor actions: you have ſeverall times met with us, pointed at us; Oh why would you not daigne to ſpeak with us? We are, we hope, of ſuch a Generation as you are, if you be, as we hope you are (notwithſtanding the tranſcendency of your paſſion) of that generation that feares God: Suppoſe the worſt, that we had wronged you (though ſhould you ſay it, we dare ſay, your conſcience would check your tongue) Oh me thinks you ſhould not recompence to us evill for evill,
Pro. 24.29. Rom. 12.17. nor thus in this vaine, frothy, wording way, ſeek to avenge your ſelfe;
Rom. 12 19. Why ſhould you be thus tranſported? You know whoſe vengeance is, and who hath ſaid he will repay; to him both you and we muſt ſtand and fall.
